{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Remediated the section-boundary BLOCK by ELIMINATING line-splicing entirely: write_jira_config now does parse(tomllib)->mutate-dict->re-emit(whole file) on a rebar-OWNED rebar.toml only. tomllib normalizes [jira]/inline-table/dotted-key to one dict, so no section-end-boundary detection and no duplicate-section hazard. One write format (rebar.toml via _emit_toml); legacy file left read-only. Also resolved advisories: probe-skip AC made explicit, --reset clears-and-exits, rebar.toml-creation rollback message, ADR added, docs reconciled, round-trip edge-case tests listed."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782782074915491001,"uuid":"8a7ece82-c7a7-43c5-8f2d-a2321de3be70"}